---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Body Parts Words — Anatomy Terms That Score High"
  description="Body part words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. THORAX (16pts), LARYNX (16pts), KNUCKLE (17pts), THYROID (14pts). Human anatomy vocabulary for competitive play."
  keywords="scrabble body parts words, thorax scrabble points, larynx scrabble, knuckle scrabble word, anatomy terms scrabble, body words scrabble, thyroid scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Body Parts Words — Anatomy Terms That Score High","description":"Body part words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. THORAX (16pts), LARYNX (16pts), KNUCKLE (17pts), THYROID (14pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-body-parts-words"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is THORAX worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"THORAX scores 16 points (T=1, H=4, O=1, R=1, A=1, X=8). The X tile provides most of the value. THORAX is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is LARYNX a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! LARYNX scores 16 points (L=1, A=1, R=1, Y=4, N=1, X=8). It refers to the voice box and is one of the highest-scoring 6-letter body part words."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What body part words use K in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"KNUCKLE (17pts), KNEECAP (15pts), ANKLE (9pts), and KIDNEY (14pts) all use the K=5 tile effectively. Body part words are surprisingly rich in K usage."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Body Parts Words — Anatomy Terms That Score High</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Human anatomy provides some of Scrabble's most reliable high-scoring words. THORAX and LARYNX each deliver 16 points, while KNUCKLE reaches 17. The body is full of X, Y, K, and H — exactly the premium letters that win games. These words are easy to remember because you carry them with you everywhere.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">KNUCKLE (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">16 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">THORAX</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">16 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">LARYNX</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">THYROID</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">X-Powered Body Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">KNUCKLE — 17 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">K=5, N=1, U=1, C=3, K=5, L=1, E=1 · 7 letters · Double K power</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">KNUCKLE uses both K tiles for a combined 10 points from that letter alone. At 17 points from 7 tiles, it's a solid play that everyone recognises. As a 7-letter word, it earns the 50-point bingo bonus if played from your full rack — making it a potential 67-point monster.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🫁 THORAX</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">16 pts · T=1, H=4, O=1, R=1, A=1, X=8 · Chest cavity</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🗣️ LARYNX</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">16 pts · L=1, A=1, R=1, Y=4, N=1, X=8 · Voice box</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🦴 PELVIS</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · P=3, E=1, L=1, V=4, I=1, S=1 · Hip bone</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧠 CORTEX</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">15 pts · C=3, O=1, R=1, T=1, E=1, X=8 · Brain outer layer</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">H and Y Body Words</h2>
      <p>The H=4 and Y=4 tiles appear frequently in anatomy terms:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">THYROID</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">THIGH</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">KIDNEY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">THUMB</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CHEEK</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WRIST</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Common Body Words (5-11 Points)</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💪 BICEP</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · B=3, I=1, C=3, E=1, P=3 · Arm muscle</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🦵 ANKLE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · A=1, N=1, K=5, L=1, E=1 · Joint</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">👃 NASAL</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">5 pts · N=1, A=1, S=1, A=1, L=1 · Nose-related</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🫀 AORTA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">5 pts · A=1, O=1, R=1, T=1, A=1 · Main artery</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Body Part Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">THORAX and LARYNX for X placement:</span> Both score 16 points and use X at the end, which is ideal for hitting premium squares in the rightmost columns. The -AX and -YNX endings connect well to existing words.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">KNUCKLE for bingo potential:</span> As a 7-letter word worth 17 points, KNUCKLE earns 67 with the bingo bonus. If you hold K, N, U, C, K, L, E — play it immediately.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">THYROID uses difficult tiles well:</span> T=1, H=4, Y=4, R=1, O=1, I=1, D=2 — THYROID turns a TH+Y combination into 14 points. When your rack has H and Y together, think anatomy.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Body part words are <span class="text-white font-medium">X and K specialists</span>. THORAX, LARYNX, and CORTEX all end in X — memorise this pattern. KNUCKLE, KIDNEY, and KNEECAP leverage K. When you draw X or K, think of the human body first.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-body-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Body Words</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-x-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best X Words for Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-medical-terms/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Medical Terms Valid in Scrabble</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid body part word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
